cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on natural language generation and understanding, specifically on discourse coherence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also describes the use of neural models, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of latent-variable Markovian generative models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses coherence evaluations, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
